{
  "info": {
    "name": "SytTech Scheduler — Full Test Suite",
    "_postman_id": "9b1c0f6e-3a7d-4d8c-9b3f-1e6a5b2c0001",
    "description": "Collection completa para o **SytTech Scheduler Service**.\n\n## Como usar\n1. Suba a stack: `docker compose up -d --build`\n2. Importe esta collection no Postman.\n3. Selecione o environment **SytTech Local** (criado automaticamente — ver variáveis na aba Variables).\n4. Rode a pasta **00 - Health & Setup** primeiro, depois **01 - Auth Flow**, **02 - Catálogo**, etc.\n5. Use o **Collection Runner** para rodar tudo em sequência (`Run collection` → `Run SytTech Scheduler`).\n\n## Encadeamento\nOs requests escrevem variáveis nas seguintes etapas:\n- `register-customer` → grava `customerId`\n- `login` → grava `accessToken`, `refreshToken`\n- `list-units` → grava `unitId`\n- `list-categories` → grava `categoryId`\n- `list-services` → grava `serviceId`\n- `list-professionals` → grava `professionalId`\n- `availability` → grava `slotStart`, `slotEnd`\n- `create-hold` → grava `holdId`\n- `confirm-appointment` → grava `appointmentId`, `appointmentCode`\n\n## Variáveis\n- `baseUrl` (default `http://localhost:8082`)\n- `email` / `password` (default `weslleytest+{{$timestamp}}@gmail.com`)\n- Tokens e IDs são preenchidos automaticamente pelos scripts.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:8082", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "email", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "password", "value": "Senha@1234", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "accessToken", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "refreshToken", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "customerId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "unitId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "categoryId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "serviceId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "professionalId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "slotStart", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "slotEnd", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "holdId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "appointmentId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "appointmentCode", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "verifyToken", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Gera um e-mail único por execução se ainda não existir",
          "if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('email')) {",
          "    const stamp = Date.now();",
          "    pm.collectionVariables.set('email', `weslleytest+${stamp}@example.com`);",
          "}"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "00 - Health & Setup",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /actuator/health",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/actuator/health", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["actuator", "health"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('status=UP', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().status).to.eql('UP'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "01 - Customers & Email Verification",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /customers — registrar (happy path → dispara e-mail real)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"fullName\": \"Weslley Teste\",\n  \"email\": \"{{email}}\",\n  \"phone\": \"+5511999990000\",\n  \"password\": \"{{password}}\",\n  \"acceptTerms\": true\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/customers", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["customers"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('201 Created', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('contém id', () => pm.expect(j.id).to.be.a('string'));",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('customerId', j.id);",
                  "console.log('customerId =', j.id);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /customers — erro 422 (sem acceptTerms)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"fullName\": \"Sem Aceite\",\n  \"email\": \"bad+{{$timestamp}}@example.com\",\n  \"phone\": \"+5511999990001\",\n  \"password\": \"Senha@1234\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/customers", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["customers"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('422 Unprocessable', () => pm.response.to.have.status(422));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /customers — erro 409 (e-mail duplicado)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"fullName\": \"Duplicado\",\n  \"email\": \"{{email}}\",\n  \"phone\": \"+5511999990002\",\n  \"password\": \"Senha@1234\",\n  \"acceptTerms\": true\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/customers", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["customers"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('409 ou 422 (depende do mapeamento)', () => pm.expect([409, 422]).to.include(pm.response.code));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /customers/verify-email — token inválido (404/422)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{ \"token\": \"token-invalido-xxx\" }" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/customers/verify-email", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["customers", "verify-email"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('erro 4xx', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([400, 404, 422]));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /customers/verify-email — happy path (preencha {{verifyToken}})",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{ \"token\": \"{{verifyToken}}\" }" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/customers/verify-email", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["customers", "verify-email"] },
            "description": "Pegue o token do e-mail recebido (link `/auth/verify?token=...`) e coloque na variável `verifyToken` da collection antes de rodar."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.collectionVariables.get('verifyToken')) {",
                  "    pm.test('204 No Content', () => pm.response.to.have.status(204));",
                  "} else {",
                  "    pm.test.skip('skip: defina verifyToken antes');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "02 - Auth (Login & Refresh)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /auth/login — happy path",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{password}}\"\n}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["auth", "login"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('tokens presentes', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(j.accessToken).to.be.a('string');",
                  "    pm.expect(j.refreshToken).to.be.a('string');",
                  "    pm.expect(j.tokenType).to.eql('Bearer');",
                  "});",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', j.accessToken);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('refreshToken', j.refreshToken);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /auth/login — 401 senha errada",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"errada\"\n}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["auth", "login"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": ["pm.test('401', () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));"]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /auth/login — 422 campos faltando",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["auth", "login"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": ["pm.test('422', () => pm.response.to.have.status(422));"]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /auth/refresh — happy path",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{ \"refreshToken\": \"{{refreshToken}}\" }" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["auth", "refresh"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('novo accessToken', () => pm.expect(j.accessToken).to.be.a('string'));",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', j.accessToken);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('refreshToken', j.refreshToken);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /auth/refresh — 401 token inválido",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{ \"refreshToken\": \"abc.def.ghi\" }" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["auth", "refresh"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": ["pm.test('401', () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));"]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /auth/refresh — 422 campo faltando",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["auth", "refresh"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": ["pm.test('422', () => pm.response.to.have.status(422));"]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "03 - Catálogo (Units / Categories / Services / Professionals)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /units — listar unidades",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/units", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["units"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "const arr = Array.isArray(j) ? j : (j.units || j.content || []);",
                  "if (arr.length) { pm.collectionVariables.set('unitId', arr[0].id); console.log('unitId =', arr[0].id); }",
                  "pm.test('lista de unidades', () => pm.expect(arr).to.be.an('array'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /units/{unitId} — detalhe",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/units/{{unitId}}", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["units", "{{unitId}}"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('unitId')) { pm.test.skip('sem unitId'); return; }",
                  "pm.test('200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /units/{unitId} — 404 inexistente",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/units/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["units", "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": ["pm.test('404', () => pm.response.to.have.status(404));"]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /units/{unitId}/categories",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/units/{{unitId}}/categories", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["units", "{{unitId}}", "categories"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('unitId')) { pm.test.skip('sem unitId'); return; }",
                  "pm.test('200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "const arr = Array.isArray(j) ? j : (j.categories || j.content || []);",
                  "if (arr.length) { pm.collectionVariables.set('categoryId', arr[0].id); console.log('categoryId =', arr[0].id); }"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /units/{unitId}/categories/{categoryId}/services",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/units/{{unitId}}/categories/{{categoryId}}/services",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["units", "{{unitId}}", "categories", "{{categoryId}}", "services"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('categoryId')) { pm.test.skip('sem categoryId'); return; }",
                  "pm.test('200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "const arr = Array.isArray(j) ? j : (j.services || j.content || []);",
                  "if (arr.length) { pm.collectionVariables.set('serviceId', arr[0].id); console.log('serviceId =', arr[0].id); }"
